[Super Street Fighter 2 Turbo Codes\Player 1 Attack Modifier]
author=BigBossman
description=With most button presses, the selected character will perform a designated light, medium, or heavy attack. In some cases, depending on what the modifier is set at, with rapid button presses, you can do a combo attack that normally wouldn't connect. For example, if you were to have the modifier set at "01" for medium attacks, rapidly pressing the set heavy punch button would cause you to do a medium punch & will sometimes have a heavy punch to follow right after. This doesn't affect the CPU. This also won't affect jumping attacks or special moves. 
Values -
00 - Light Punches & Kicks
01 - Medium Punches & Kicks
02 - Heavy Punches & Kicks
patch=1,EE,0084C2DE,extended,00000001

[Super Street Fighter 2 Turbo Codes\Player 1 Can't Walk]
author=BigBossman
description=This is designed to handicap the player. The player won't be able to walk back or forth, but can still move by jumping or by using a special move.
patch=1,EE,0084C190,extended,00000001

[Super Street Fighter 2 Turbo Codes\Player 1 Can't Win Rounds]
author=BigBossman
description=
patch=1,EE,0084C4EE,extended,00000000

[Super Street Fighter 2 Turbo Codes\Player 1 Character Modifier]
author=BigBossman
description=Akuma would ordinarily be at Value "10", but doesn't work. It causes the game to freeze. This modifier is a character select type modifier, by keeping the cursor in a specific spot. Use Values "00" to "0F".
Values - 
00 - Ryu
01 - E. Honda
02 - Blanka
03 - Guile
04 - Ken
05 - Chun-Li
06 - Zangief
07 - Dhalsim
08 - M. Bison
09 - Sagat
0A - Balrog
0B - Vega
0C - Cammy
0D - T. Hawk
0E - Fei Long
0F - Dee Jay
10 - FROZE
patch=1,EE,0084C4EF,extended,00000000

[Super Street Fighter 2 Turbo Codes\Player 1 gets KOed with 1-Hit]
author=BigBossman
description=The first clean hit will KO Player 1. You can block special moves or counter & it won't cause a KO. When the player gets KOed, the screen goes dark & the next round will start. The screen won't go dark if you KO the CPU. Also the game will reset after playing through to Balrog. 
patch=1,EE,0084C1D6,extended,00000001

[Super Street Fighter 2 Turbo Codes\Player 1 Gravity Modifier]
author=BigBossman
description=This can make the player lighter or heavier depending on what value you use. Using Value "7F" will cause the character to jump higher than normal & may even cause their moves to be performed higher up than usual. Ryu & Ken's spin kick (when performed on the ground) will go about 3/4 of the way up. Their dragon punch will also go further up too. When using Value "00", characters can't get off the ground when they jump, Ryu & Ken's spin kick is done at ground level & hits lower than it normally does, & Ryu & Ken's dragon punch doesn't go very high at all. If you set the value too high, they characters will jump & not come back down. There is a potential that when a player is knocked down, they will float upward & not come back down. This depends on the value setting.
patch=1,EE,0084C19D,extended,00000000

[Super Street Fighter 2 Turbo Codes\Player 1 Has No Boundaries]
author=BigBossman
description=The player can walk, be thrown, or jump beyond the limits of the stage in either direction. If you go back too far, it will cause you to loop back around, however, you won't be able to hit the other player unless they go beyond far enough with you. Also once you loop back around, fireballs can only hit when the other player is up close. This also makes it impossible for Vega to perform his swan dive & air suplex & also makes it impossible for Vega & Chun-Li to do a triangle jump.
patch=1,EE,0084C2FB,extended,00000001

[Super Street Fighter 2 Turbo Codes\Player 1 Jumping Disabled]
author=BigBossman
description=The player can perform their special moves without any problems, but will not be able to perform regular jumping attacks or won't be able to jump over enemy projectiles. This doesn't affect the CPU.
patch=1,EE,0084C30B,extended,00000001

[Super Street Fighter 2 Turbo Codes\Player 1 Projectiles Disabled]
author=BigBossman
description=This affects Ryu (including his Super Hadoken), Ken, Chun-Li, Guile, Sagat (both high & low Tiger Shots), Dee Jay, & Dhalsim (including his Yoga Flame). This also works on the CPU.
patch=1,EE,0084C332,extended,00000001

[Super Street Fighter 2 Turbo Codes\Player 1 Rapid Punches]
author=BigBossman
description=Tends to make choosing your character a bit harder since the cursor move faster. The cursor won't move right, but can move left, up, & down.
patch=1,EE,0084C4F1,extended,00000001

[Super Street Fighter 2 Turbo Codes\Player 1 Turbo & Attack Style]
author=BigBossman
description=This makes the player's animations super fast & also causes up-close standing attacks to be used even if you are further away.
patch=1,EE,0084C1C1,extended,00000001

[Super Street Fighter 2 Turbo Codes\Player 1 Vega Claw Modifier]
author=BigBossman
description=Values -
00 - Claw is Missing 
01 - Claw is Always On
patch=1,EE,0084C2AA,extended,00000000

[Super Street Fighter 2 Turbo Codes\Player 1's Button Hold Color is Always Active]
author=BigBossman
description=Nothing spectacular. This just causes you to use the color of a character as if you held a button for two seconds. If Player 1 & Player 2 choose the same character, the who chooses the character last will select the next color.
patch=1,EE,0084C1DE,extended,00000001

[Super Street Fighter 2 Turbo Codes\Player 1's Special Move Modifier]
author=BigBossman
description=This messes with the player's special moves. It doesn't seem to affect the CPU. It affects different characters differently. Some might get stuck temporarily until hit before or after performing a special move. Others may not be able to perform certain moves. This mostly seems to affect Ryu & Ken. It causes them to shoot a fireball after performing a dragon punch & spin kick. This also has noticeable effect on Chun-Li's spin kick also.
patch=1,EE,0084C1E6,extended,00000001

